Editor's note: This report focuses on Chongqing as part of our special series, "Rising Star Cities," about Chinese cities whose annual GDP exceeds 1 trillion yuan ($155.4 billion, or more than the GDP of Qatar). At the end of 2020, there were 23 such cities. Click here for more stories on Chongqing. You can also explore our earlier coverage of Ningbo and Changsha. Southwest China's Chongqing Municipality has become a popular destination for filming movies due to its unique landscape and culture. Its high-rise buildings, subways and bridges built near the mountain create a unique layout. The imaginative designs feature various geometric shapes. Check out some film locations and see if you can identify the movie scenes.